These data sets describe different gun related information for the US.

---------------------------------------------------

1. cdc.firearm.mortality.data.csv - approximately 21.45 kB

Source: Center for Disease Control

Columns
YEAR - data runs from 2005 to 2019, not all years covered
STATE - abbreviated US States
RATE - rate of deaths per 100,000 
DEATHS - deaths in that year
URL - All data from CDC, attach the prefix "https://www.cdc.gov/" to each URL

----------------------------------------------------

2. 2020.gun.violence.archive.csv

Source: 
Gun Violence Archive 
1133 Connecticut Avenue, NW
Washington, DC 20036
inquiry@gva.us.com
@gundeaths
https://www.gunviolencearchive.org/

Columns
Incident ID	-
Incident Date - Mass shootings between Jan.1 2020 and Dec.31 2020
State - US full state name
City Or County - 
Address	- Street address in City or County
# Killed - number killed
# Injured - number injured	
Operations - NA

-----------------------------------------------------

